  },
  {
    "verifyText": {
      "id": "lf_help_6",
      "value": "Variable life insurance policies pay a death benefit to your beneficiary when you die. Policy coverage continues as long as you pay premiums. Your premium is based on actuarial statistics for your age and health characteristics."
    }
  },
  {
    "verifyText": {
      "id": "lf_help_7",
      "value": "While your policy is in effect, it accrues a cash value, which can be used as collateral at an interest rate stated in the policy agreement. Any loans that are outstanding at the time of your death reduce the amount of the death benefit."
    }
  },
  {
    "verifyText": {
      "id": "lf_help_8",
      "value": "If you cancel a variable life policy, you are sometimes faced with a surrender charge, particularly if the policy is held for only a short time. A key feature of variable life insurance policies is that the premium can be skipped if the insurer's investment performance is good enough to fund your premium payment."
